title: 107_hr4532
content: DISPERSE ORANGE 30, DISPERSE BLUE 79:1, DISPERSE RED 167:1, DISPERSE YELLOW 64, DISPERSE RED 60, DISPERSE BLUE 60, DISPERSE BLUE 77, DISPERSE YELLOW 42, DISPERSE RED 86, AND DISPERSE RED 86:1 are added to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States includes additions of Propanenitrile and Acetamide compounds by specified dates. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States includes additions of various chemical compounds by specified dates, such as bromo-4,6-dinitrophenyl-azo-4-methoxyphenyl, Acetamide N-[5-[bis[2-(acetyloxy)ethyl]amino]-2-[(2-chloro-4-nitrophenyl)azo]phenyl], and 1H-Indene. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States includes additions of various chemical compounds by specified dates, such as 1,3(2H)-dione, 2-(4-bromo-3-hydroxy-2-quinolinyl), 9,10-Anthra-cenedione, and 1H-Naphth[2,3. The curr_chunk provides information on chemical compounds including isoindole-1,3,5,10(2H)-tetrone and 9,10-Anthracenedione. These compounds are classified under specific subheadings in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The curr_chunk provides details on chemical compounds like Benzenesulfonamide and N-(4-amino-9,10-dihydro-3-methoxy-9,10-dioxo-1-anthracenyl)-4-methyl-. These compounds are listed under specific subheadings in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The curr_chunk provides information on Benzenesulfonamide and N-(4-amino-9,10-dihydro-3-methoxy-9,10-dioxo-1-anthracenyl) chemical compounds listed under specific subheadings in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The amendment made by subsection (a) applies to goods entered or withdrawn from warehouse for consumption on or after the 15th day after the enactment of this Act.
